<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n12068h"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12068h">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12068h"> 68(h)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> ~ Quand il eut quitt&eacute; ses / habits sacerdoteaux le bon / abb&eacute; prodigua certainement / des paroles de consolation / &agrave; l&apos;infortun&eacute; conn&eacute;table. / Elles, &agrave; n&apos;en pas douter, / &eacute;loquentes et persuasives: / quelques mois apr&egrave;s / Duguesclin &eacute;pousait / Jeanne de Laval</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">&hellip; Quand il eut quitt&eacute; ses habits sacerdotaux, le bon abb&eacute; prodigua certainement des paroles deconsolation &agrave; l&apos;infortun&eacute; conn&eacute;table. Elles furent, &agrave; n&apos;en pas douter, &eacute;loquentes et persuasives: quelques mois apr&egrave;s Duguesclin &eacute;pousait Jeanne de Laval. <br><font color="green">[When he had discarded his priestly vestments, the good abbot certainly lavished consolations on the unfortunate constable. These were undoubtedly eloquent and persuasive: a few months later Duguesclin married Jeanne de Laval.]</font> <small> &Eacute;tienne Dupont, <a name="SMIN" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#SMIN"><cite title="source">Le Mont Saint-Michel Inconnu</cite></a> (1912) 235-6</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Raphael transcription: <a name="c12060e" href="c12all.htm#c12060e">VI.C.12:060(e)</a></mm></dd> </dd></dl>
